Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.25,0:00:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you get stoned out all the time. It's very hard to get past these flowers. I
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.02,0:01:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,purposely avoid looking at these flowers because they are so... it makes you break
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.10,0:01:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,out in tears. How beautiful music makes you break out in tears. You can't prove
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.98,0:01:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the aesthetic, exquisite joy that you experience out of beauty. It's not within
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.56,0:01:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the linear domain. I got talking about beauty and you see it happens. I'm not
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.79,0:01:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,going to look at beauty anymore. It has a positive effect, you know, on your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.73,0:01:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,neuronal connections. The best preparation for your children is the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.64,0:02:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual, religious experiences of the child and aesthetic beauty, beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.29,0:02:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,music, and appreciation of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.60,0:02:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I was partitioned for beauty, you know, so I myself, that was a part of my religious
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.53,0:02:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,upbringing... was a constant exposure to beauty. Both my parents were musicians,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.46,0:02:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was a member of the Art Institute, and I played violin and piano, and I was a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.96,0:02:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,soloist, a boy soprano, and I remember being in a Greek Cathedral, and I sang the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.47,0:02:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,obbligato upon us angelicas in this soprano.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.63,0:02:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a high soprano voice, I had a high soprano, said, there you are in the Greek cathedral,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.25,0:02:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,stained glass windows, the sunlight is coming in and lighting up the clouds of incense,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.77,0:03:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a full choir and a full orchestra at this cathedral, and here, this voice came through
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.90,0:03:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.90,0:03:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the soprano obbligato, very high obbligato, vocal, choir, orchestra, and a presence sang.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.08,0:03:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a presence, that sang.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.00,0:03:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It wipes you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.00,0:03:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't think about such things when you're giving a lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.52,0:03:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We're back to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.49,0:03:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to put together a book of slides, we now have about 110 of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.25,0:03:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time we give a new lecture in Sedona, it creates a whole new slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.18,0:03:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Next one we're going to do on the miraculous, and we'll talk about the miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.96,0:03:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.71,0:03:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.90,0:04:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This looks too academic, she says, that's too complicated, we'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.06,0:04:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic people, just being decent human beings, what do you have to do to evolve spiritually?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.36,0:04:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I say the best thing to do is to be kind to all of life and all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.93,0:04:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Be kind to all, and a pervasive goodwill towards yourself and towards life, so goodwill means
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.55,0:04:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,towards your own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.06,0:04:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Towards your own life, goodwill, and appreciation for its beauty, and to see your own life as
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.38,0:04:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.63,0:04:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That leads to a style of life which is contemplated.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.02,0:04:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation has its place, and I've spent many years meditating on a regular basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.67,0:04:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Contemplation is putting into practice spiritual principles to such an extent that you eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.50,0:04:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,become that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.50,0:04:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not something you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.16,0:05:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.56,0:05:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What you are is loving, and gentle, and supportive, and exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.93,0:05:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we all cried this morning, everybody I was greeting, I just went into a state of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.23,0:05:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,joy, they went into a state of joy, and we're both crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.75,0:05:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to get through a whole crowd, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.07,0:05:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone was just being the reality of their essence, that's all they were doing, just
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.24,0:05:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,being what they actually are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.07,0:05:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Safety is when you can just be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.12,0:05:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What you really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.14,0:05:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So these things may not be acceptable in the modern, so-called post-modern world, but these
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.24,0:05:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,are what I grew up in, in middle America, Wisconsin, 1930s, around in there, 20s.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.77,0:06:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought everybody was like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.24,0:06:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, there's only two kinds of people in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.24,0:06:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There were people who were different.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.24,0:06:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There were people who were different.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.24,0:06:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There were people who were different.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.74,0:06:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There were people who were different.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.83,0:06:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There were people who were different.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.95,0:06:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There were people who were decent, honest, pleasant, respectable, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.45,0:06:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there were gangsters, Machine Gun Kelly, and Babyface Nelson, and the Mafia
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.02,0:06:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,guys in Chicago, the liquor guys, I forget what their names, Scarface.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.97,0:06:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there were, then there was the people that everybody was dependable, they tried
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.25,0:06:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to get there on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.44,0:06:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They tried to be responsible for their own emotions and not pour them all over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.91,0:06:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody tried to be neat and fair and ethical and humane towards animals and everybody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.12,0:06:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was gracious towards everybody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.39,0:07:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody tried to be modest, diplomatic, polite, firm, and nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.29,0:07:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But what you can see when we calibrated the level of consciousness of mankind, what I
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.50,0:07:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,consider to be the norm, is frankly the exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.24,0:07:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Being sold to the earth is now sort of, I guess, exceptional, to be easy going, to let
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.04,0:07:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,people off the hook.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.04,0:07:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you got them on the hook, so why not let them off the hook, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.04,0:07:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not let people off the hook and forgive them because people just don't know any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.00,0:07:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so let's move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.50,0:07:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the, to clarify what's going on in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.04,0:07:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mind is 99% silent, 99% of your mind is silent, 1% is what you're listening to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.32,0:08:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look underneath thought, you'll see that underneath the thinkingness, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.79,0:08:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the noise going on in your mind, there is an infinite stillness, an infinite profound
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.69,0:08:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,stillness and silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.10,0:08:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 99% of your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.42,0:08:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 99% of your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.42,0:08:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 99% of your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.36,0:08:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 99% of your mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.99,0:08:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of bemoaning the fact that you can't seem to get your mind to stop thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.01,0:08:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,what I advise people to do is stop trying to, don't try to get your mind to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.18,0:08:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, look beneath the mind and you'll see that beneath the mind is an infinite field
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.68,0:08:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.62,0:08:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If it were not for the infinite field of silence, you wouldn't know what you were thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.89,0:08:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The television set is blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.44,0:08:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't, when you turn it on, it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.67,0:08:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It lights up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.59,0:08:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So if it wasn't for the field, you wouldn't know what you're seeing on the set.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.47,0:08:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So your mind is like 99% silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.46,0:09:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like walking through the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.48,0:09:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The woods is actually silent, and the fact that you hear a bird, the reason you hear
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.13,0:09:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the bird is not because of the song and the bird, but because of the silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.65,0:09:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If it weren't for the silence, you couldn't hear the bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.98,0:09:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.98,0:09:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If it weren't for the fact that your mind is intrinsically silent, you wouldn't know
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.62,0:09:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.62,0:09:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So look and become at one with the silence, the infinite non-linear silence, and that's
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.67,0:09:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,part of your life becoming a prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.00,0:09:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the mind is always busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.79,0:09:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Look what it's doing here all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.15,0:09:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is turn on everybody's, turn on any night's television.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.62,0:09:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.62,0:09:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a big contest amongst victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.83,0:09:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Who can be the best?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.83,0:09:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Who can be the worst?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.71,0:09:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Who can be the biggest victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.59,0:09:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There's two contests.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.59,0:09:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,One is to be the world's biggest victim and get the greatest sympathy, and the other is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.44,0:09:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.37,0:10:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,People will do anything to be right, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.33,0:10:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is what the mind is doing to keep itself busy, and we said what keeps the thing
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.47,0:10:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,going is the juice you're getting off of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.78,0:10:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way to disconnect the mind is to look and see what kind of juice you're getting
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.11,0:10:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,out of these thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.02,0:10:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to give up the thoughts, memories, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.47,0:10:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to give up the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.11,0:10:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to only give up the juice that you're getting off of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.09,0:10:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The same as hate or any other thing that you don't want to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.28,0:10:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, am I willing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.57,0:10:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to be willing to give up hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.69,0:10:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.02,0:10:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hatred pays off so good in our current world you can't do without it, but we're willing
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.67,0:10:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to give up the juice that you're getting out of the hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.84,0:10:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So once you give up the juice of resentment, self-pity, guilt, you're going to have to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.17,0:10:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,give up the juice that you're getting out of the hatred, self-pity, guilt, self-pity,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.72,0:10:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.72,0:10:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize how narcissistic guilt is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.72,0:10:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Walling around, oh me, oh bad me, why I'm so awful, oh sackcloth and ashes, oh penance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.72,0:10:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how narcissistic it is, don't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.07,0:11:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not doing this for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.07,0:11:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, penance for God, sackcloth and ashes, oh woe is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.32,0:11:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now why would God be happy with that, unless he was a sadist of some kind, pervert or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.50,0:11:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Gets a kick out of your suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.00,0:11:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.86,0:11:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, this is what the mind does.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.29,0:11:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It moralizes, and you see, the great contest in today's world is for moral, it's a moral
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.42,0:11:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.42,0:11:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you read the evening news, the world is engaged in an endless of who's got the moral
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.09,0:11:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,high ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.58,0:11:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's got the moral high ground?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.58,0:11:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The clash of civilizations is who's got the moral high ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.13,0:11:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The clash of politics, Democrats, Republicans, all the rest of them, is who's got the moral
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.79,0:11:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,high ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.79,0:11:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an endless contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.14,0:11:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the endless contest for the moral high ground, because the moral high ground now
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.49,0:12:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,gives you permission to do whatever the moral, you think the moral high ground justifies
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.21,0:12:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,your doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.21,0:12:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Killing infidels or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.42,0:12:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably a good idea to kill all infidels, come to think of it, I never thought of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.20,0:12:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a smart idea, it keeps you busy for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.54,0:12:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Killing all the infidels is going to keep you busy for quite a few centuries, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.87,0:12:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of infidels running around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.87,0:12:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All over the place, every rock is hiding an infidel behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.53,0:12:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.53,0:12:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Functions of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.53,0:12:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, this is the mind, the energy fuels, those of you who are familiar with the etheric
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.65,0:12:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,energy fuels and chakras, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.85,0:12:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a concentration at lower mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.07,0:12:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Lower mind calibrates about 190, 160, 165.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.60,0:12:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the world of relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.39,0:12:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.39,0:12:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrates below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.47,0:13:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativism does not appeal to people who calibrate higher over 200, especially 275.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.28,0:13:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It also doesn't appeal to people who have a reasonably good IQ.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.69,0:13:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So higher mind looks at abstraction, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.90,0:13:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks at abstraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.90,0:13:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks at generalities, so it's able to stratify and go from just the linear pedestrian,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.69,0:13:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the inference, the abstract inference.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.12,0:13:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.62,0:13:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This is lower mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.58,0:13:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This kind of thinking is what characterizes the media, competition and greed and force
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.98,0:13:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and exploiting things, insensitivity, etc., constantly wanting something.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.41,0:13:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Higher mind sees things not in terms of what their cash is, but their true value.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.32,0:14:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees potential, so higher mind is more into aesthetics, it's more intuitive, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.32,0:14:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,actually more intelligent, and it looks to serve life, it looks to serve life, looks
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.52,0:14:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve life.
